<p>You can definitely connect 2 data ports of ws2812 strips to the same IO pin on an Arduino/Rio and it will mirror the strips. But you can have some strange side effects.</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":22,"updated_at":"2024-10-15T08:15:44.742Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":116,"readers_count":115,"score":28.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":473063,"topic_slug":"addressable-leds-help","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":62434,"username":"Strflightmight","name":"Ezra","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/strflightmight/{size}/261969_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":43037,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Mentor - 4253 Raid Zero / 8503 Raid One (Taiwan)"},"post_url":"/t/addressable-leds-help/473063/9","custom_user_title":"Mentor - 4253 Raid Zero / 8503 Raid One (Taiwan)","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3435074,"name":"Ezra","username":"Strflightmight","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/strflightmight/{size}/261969_2.png","created_at":"2024-10-15T08:24:29.349Z","cooked":"<p>We don’t want to mirror them though. Are there any other options? What did you mean before by connecting a single LED?</p>","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"posts_count":22,"updated_at":"2024-10-15T08:24:29.349Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":108,"readers_count":107,"score":26.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":473063,"topic_slug":"addressable-leds-help","display_username":"Ezra","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":43037,"username":"ProbablyWont","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/e19adc/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62434,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"5990 | Programmer, Electronics Lead, and Driver"},"post_url":"/t/addressable-leds-help/473063/10","custom_user_title":"5990 | Programmer, Electronics Lead, and Driver","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3435077,"name":"sam liu","username":"catrix","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/dbc845/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-10-15T09:02:16.002Z","cooked":"<p>If you connect them in series, you should treat them as one LED stripe with 2x the original length. The stripe connected to your robotRIO can be controlled normally.  But for the stripe connected to that stripe, you would have to map the address from <code>i</code> to <code>i+n</code> where n is the length.</p>","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"posts_count":22,"updated_at":"2024-10-15T09:03:08.542Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":106,"readers_count":105,"score":26.2,"yours